1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:01,800
 Have a seat, have a seat.

2
00:00:01,800 --> 00:00:02,760
 It's so good that you're here.

3
00:00:02,760 --> 00:00:04,200
 My name's Andrew, I'm one of the pastors.

4
00:00:04,200 --> 00:00:06,360
 If you're joining us online for the first time,

5
00:00:06,360 --> 00:00:08,700
 or if you're in this room in the overflow,

6
00:00:08,700 --> 00:00:11,520
 joining us for the first time, we're so glad you're with us.

7
00:00:11,520 --> 00:00:13,360
 We're in a series called Public Faith,

8
00:00:13,360 --> 00:00:16,400
 and we're really unpacking through scripture

9
00:00:16,400 --> 00:00:18,640
 what we've just been praying about.

10
00:00:18,640 --> 00:00:22,480
 This wonderful opportunity we have in the world right now

11
00:00:22,480 --> 00:00:24,960
 to see the gospel of Jesus take root

12
00:00:24,960 --> 00:00:27,760
 and take hold like never before.

13
00:00:28,760 --> 00:00:32,040
 And there's this really profound moment

14
00:00:32,040 --> 00:00:36,960
 where the apostle Paul writes into the church in Rome.

15
00:00:36,960 --> 00:00:39,520
 And in the very first chapter of his letter

16
00:00:39,520 --> 00:00:43,080
 to the church in Rome, Paul writes a very short little verse

17
00:00:43,080 --> 00:00:45,720
 but it's a verse that really unpacks,

18
00:00:45,720 --> 00:00:48,760
 I think, his manifesto for public faith,

19
00:00:48,760 --> 00:00:53,760
 his manifesto for why we should live our faith publicly.

20
00:00:53,760 --> 00:00:57,280
 And in so doing, he's, with this one little verse,

21
00:00:57,280 --> 00:01:00,680
 trying to instill confidence and boldness

22
00:01:00,680 --> 00:01:03,580
 and courage in the church in Rome.

23
00:01:03,580 --> 00:01:07,560
 Now, the church in Rome, as far as we were aware,

24
00:01:07,560 --> 00:01:10,820
 at the time of Paul's writing to it, was relatively small.

25
00:01:10,820 --> 00:01:12,160
 In fact, from what we can tell,

26
00:01:12,160 --> 00:01:15,480
 it was largely gathering in three small houses.

27
00:01:15,480 --> 00:01:20,000
 It was three small house churches in the city of Rome.

28
00:01:20,000 --> 00:01:22,460
 I wonder if you could imagine for a moment

29
00:01:22,460 --> 00:01:26,000
 what it would have been like to be a Christian,

30
00:01:26,000 --> 00:01:29,080
 to bear witness to the gospel of Jesus

31
00:01:29,080 --> 00:01:34,080
 in the very epicenter of Greco-Roman empire and power.

32
00:01:34,080 --> 00:01:39,160
 The whole of Rome was designed

33
00:01:39,160 --> 00:01:43,300
 to speak forth a proclamation about power.

34
00:01:43,300 --> 00:01:45,840
 The phrase, "All roads lead to Rome,"

35
00:01:45,840 --> 00:01:47,880
 was actually literally true.

36
00:01:47,880 --> 00:01:50,960
 And everything funneled in the city, the architecture,

37
00:01:50,960 --> 00:01:53,640
 the structure of the city in those days,

38
00:01:53,640 --> 00:01:56,080
 all of it, the social structures and the social norms,

39
00:01:56,080 --> 00:01:58,040
 all of it was designed to bring you

40
00:01:58,040 --> 00:02:03,040
 to the very center of that power, which was Caesar himself.

41
00:02:03,040 --> 00:02:07,560
 And from Caesar, all of that power and that authority

42
00:02:07,560 --> 00:02:10,800
 and the dominion of the empire went from Caesar

43
00:02:10,800 --> 00:02:13,960
 back out to the rest of the Greco-Roman empire.

44
00:02:13,960 --> 00:02:16,920
 So imagine what it would be like for you

45
00:02:16,920 --> 00:02:18,880
 to be somebody who was right there

46
00:02:18,880 --> 00:02:22,040
 in the epicenter of that power,

47
00:02:22,040 --> 00:02:24,140
 believing in a different kind of power.

48
00:02:24,140 --> 00:02:29,440
 Imagine how it must have felt to be embedded

49
00:02:29,440 --> 00:02:31,440
 as a little piece of yeast

50
00:02:31,440 --> 00:02:35,000
 in this massive amount of dough around you.

51
00:02:35,000 --> 00:02:37,480
 And you would be forgiven for thinking

52
00:02:37,480 --> 00:02:39,800
 that those people in those house churches,

53
00:02:39,800 --> 00:02:43,780
 probably many of them new believers in Jesus,

54
00:02:43,780 --> 00:02:46,700
 were pretty happy when they were in the safety

55
00:02:46,700 --> 00:02:50,080
 and the security of those house church gatherings

56
00:02:50,080 --> 00:02:52,560
 to profess their relationship with Jesus.

57
00:02:52,560 --> 00:02:55,020
 But you could understand that as soon as they stepped out

58
00:02:55,020 --> 00:02:58,120
 of there, their desire to wanna keep pretty personal

59
00:02:58,120 --> 00:03:00,840
 and pretty private about that faith.

60
00:03:00,840 --> 00:03:06,920
 And Paul, being the bold pastor that he is,

61
00:03:06,920 --> 00:03:11,200
 writes to the church in Rome, a church he had never visited,

62
00:03:11,200 --> 00:03:14,460
 but he writes to the church in Rome

63
00:03:14,460 --> 00:03:19,460
 and he says something to them that will shake that church

64
00:03:19,720 --> 00:03:20,600
 like never before.

65
00:03:20,600 --> 00:03:22,120
 In fact, this thing that he says,

66
00:03:22,120 --> 00:03:23,840
 and then he then unpacks it

67
00:03:23,840 --> 00:03:25,500
 throughout the rest of the letter,

68
00:03:25,500 --> 00:03:27,940
 this thing that he said, they didn't know it at the time,

69
00:03:27,940 --> 00:03:31,960
 but it would become the catalyst to the greatest move

70
00:03:31,960 --> 00:03:34,240
 of the Spirit of God in the church of Rome

71
00:03:34,240 --> 00:03:36,760
 that it had ever experienced in its history

72
00:03:36,760 --> 00:03:38,400
 up until that point.

73
00:03:38,400 --> 00:03:41,320
 One little phrase.

74
00:03:41,320 --> 00:03:44,240
 You wanna know what it is?

75
00:03:44,240 --> 00:03:45,160
 Let me read it to you.

76
00:03:45,160 --> 00:03:48,180
 This is Romans chapter one, verse 16.

77
00:03:49,200 --> 00:03:53,240
 Paul says, "I am not ashamed of the gospel

78
00:03:53,240 --> 00:03:58,740
 "because it is the power of God for the salvation

79
00:03:58,740 --> 00:04:00,900
 "of everyone who believes,

80
00:04:00,900 --> 00:04:03,880
 "first for the Jew, then for the Gentile."

81
00:04:03,880 --> 00:04:10,640
 Paul writes into a church meeting behind closed doors

82
00:04:10,640 --> 00:04:15,180
 and he says, "You have to understand

83
00:04:15,180 --> 00:04:18,360
 "that we are not to be ashamed of the gospel

84
00:04:18,360 --> 00:04:20,540
 "because it is the power of God

85
00:04:20,540 --> 00:04:24,340
 "for the salvation of everyone who believes."

86
00:04:24,340 --> 00:04:27,440
 If you were to read this passage in the Greek,

87
00:04:27,440 --> 00:04:30,040
 it's neatly written in two sections,

88
00:04:30,040 --> 00:04:31,560
 the first half and the second half.

89
00:04:31,560 --> 00:04:33,680
 I wanna deal with both of those briefly.

90
00:04:33,680 --> 00:04:35,080
 The first half, he says this,

91
00:04:35,080 --> 00:04:37,720
 "I am not ashamed of the gospel,"

92
00:04:37,720 --> 00:04:40,300
 or if you read it in the Greek, it reads more like this,

93
00:04:40,300 --> 00:04:43,560
 "I am not shamed by the gospel."

94
00:04:44,840 --> 00:04:48,320
 Paul is doing something very counter-cultural

95
00:04:48,320 --> 00:04:49,160
 in this moment.

96
00:04:49,160 --> 00:04:52,560
 He takes a word, this word ashamed.

97
00:04:52,560 --> 00:04:55,960
 In the Greek, it was a word that was very central

98
00:04:55,960 --> 00:04:58,980
 to the whole of the Greek and Roman culture and society.

99
00:04:58,980 --> 00:05:03,280
 In fact, it was a word that was used very often in society.

100
00:05:03,280 --> 00:05:05,200
 You have to understand that Greek and Roman society

101
00:05:05,200 --> 00:05:08,840
 was built upon an honor-shame culture.

102
00:05:08,840 --> 00:05:10,640
 And an honor-shame culture was one

103
00:05:10,640 --> 00:05:13,680
 where people lived their lives very publicly

104
00:05:13,680 --> 00:05:17,800
 and how they were seen publicly, their reputation,

105
00:05:17,800 --> 00:05:20,280
 the way that others around them viewed them

106
00:05:20,280 --> 00:05:21,440
 was very important.

107
00:05:21,440 --> 00:05:24,560
 It was paramount to your success in that city

108
00:05:24,560 --> 00:05:28,800
 to have a good reputation or a good public persona.

109
00:05:28,800 --> 00:05:33,700
 And you did that through this process of honor and shame.

110
00:05:33,700 --> 00:05:35,560
 Honor, quite literally,

111
00:05:35,560 --> 00:05:39,840
 was the value of your worth in society.

112
00:05:39,840 --> 00:05:42,460
 And you gained honor by what you did

113
00:05:42,460 --> 00:05:44,360
 and how you conducted yourself,

114
00:05:44,360 --> 00:05:45,920
 or perhaps the wealth that you had

115
00:05:45,920 --> 00:05:49,460
 or the lineage that you were born into.

116
00:05:49,460 --> 00:05:54,000
 So honor helped you to rise in status in society.

117
00:05:54,000 --> 00:05:57,840
 Conversely, shame was the loss of honor.

118
00:05:57,840 --> 00:06:01,480
 So honor could be gained, but it could also be lost.

119
00:06:01,480 --> 00:06:03,240
 And when you are shamed,

120
00:06:03,240 --> 00:06:05,400
 it's because you had some honor before,

121
00:06:05,400 --> 00:06:06,800
 but that honor is now gone.

122
00:06:06,800 --> 00:06:09,880
 And when somebody was shamed in Greek or Roman society,

123
00:06:09,880 --> 00:06:13,420
 it was almost always public humiliation,

124
00:06:13,420 --> 00:06:15,220
 some public rejection.

125
00:06:15,220 --> 00:06:17,900
 And you could get shamed for a lot of different things,

126
00:06:17,900 --> 00:06:21,120
 maybe aligning yourself to somebody

127
00:06:21,120 --> 00:06:23,960
 who is of a low class in society,

128
00:06:23,960 --> 00:06:27,660
 maybe professing to have a belief system

129
00:06:27,660 --> 00:06:31,140
 or a thought that was different from the societal norms.

130
00:06:31,140 --> 00:06:34,620
 If you could make yourself more like the society around you,

131
00:06:34,620 --> 00:06:36,380
 you would rise in honor.

132
00:06:36,380 --> 00:06:39,520
 But as soon as you began to act, think,

133
00:06:39,520 --> 00:06:42,320
 or be different to the society around you,

134
00:06:42,320 --> 00:06:44,660
 then shame would come upon you.

135
00:06:44,660 --> 00:06:48,060
 Now here's the powerful thing.

136
00:06:48,060 --> 00:06:53,060
 The symbol of the greatest shame in Greek or Roman society

137
00:06:53,060 --> 00:06:55,220
 was the crucifixion.

138
00:06:55,220 --> 00:06:59,640
 The crucifixion was the highest punishment

139
00:06:59,640 --> 00:07:03,580
 for the lowest level of status.

140
00:07:03,580 --> 00:07:08,220
 And if anybody in your family had ever been crucified,

141
00:07:08,220 --> 00:07:12,380
 the loss of face and the shame upon you as a family

142
00:07:12,380 --> 00:07:15,540
 would last for generations.

143
00:07:15,540 --> 00:07:20,540
 So crucifixion and the impact of that for shame

144
00:07:20,540 --> 00:07:23,700
 and the loss of face was central to the understanding

145
00:07:23,700 --> 00:07:26,540
 of this Greek or Roman honor and shame culture.

146
00:07:26,540 --> 00:07:28,980
 So could you imagine what it would be like to say,

147
00:07:28,980 --> 00:07:32,460
 I follow someone who was crucified?

148
00:07:32,460 --> 00:07:34,260
 What you're essentially saying is,

149
00:07:34,260 --> 00:07:38,380
 I am following someone who has been deeply shamed

150
00:07:38,380 --> 00:07:41,060
 and rejected, which means by association,

151
00:07:41,060 --> 00:07:43,540
 I am also shamed.

152
00:07:43,540 --> 00:07:47,060
 And so you could forgive those people in the church of Rome

153
00:07:47,060 --> 00:07:50,020
 going, hey, I'm happy to confess Jesus as my Lord

154
00:07:50,020 --> 00:07:53,420
 and Savior in the nice comfort of our home church.

155
00:07:53,420 --> 00:07:55,620
 But as soon as I'm back outside there

156
00:07:55,620 --> 00:07:57,500
 in Greek or Roman society,

157
00:07:57,500 --> 00:08:00,640
 I don't want the shame of that relationship

158
00:08:00,640 --> 00:08:01,660
 to still be on me.

159
00:08:01,660 --> 00:08:04,780
 I don't want to be shamed by the gospel.

160
00:08:04,780 --> 00:08:06,460
 Are you with me?

161
00:08:06,460 --> 00:08:08,020
 No one is with me.

162
00:08:08,020 --> 00:08:08,860
 Are you with me?

163
00:08:08,860 --> 00:08:12,380
 Paul writes into that and he says,

164
00:08:12,380 --> 00:08:14,180
 here's the thing you need to know right up front.

165
00:08:14,180 --> 00:08:15,980
 I've got a long letter and I'm gonna unpack this

166
00:08:15,980 --> 00:08:18,220
 in a lot of detail, but here's the summary of it.

167
00:08:18,220 --> 00:08:20,700
 I am not ashamed of the gospel.

168
00:08:20,700 --> 00:08:25,740
 In other words, I am not shamed by the gospel,

169
00:08:25,740 --> 00:08:29,860
 which is incredibly powerful

170
00:08:29,860 --> 00:08:31,140
 because what he's trying to do

171
00:08:31,140 --> 00:08:34,500
 is not just subvert a Greek or Roman system,

172
00:08:34,500 --> 00:08:36,740
 but he's actually trying to show the church

173
00:08:36,740 --> 00:08:39,620
 why they should be bold and courageous

174
00:08:39,620 --> 00:08:42,780
 because what they profess is actually the thing

175
00:08:42,780 --> 00:08:45,700
 that that system desperately needs.

176
00:08:45,700 --> 00:08:47,780
 Now, to understand that,

177
00:08:47,780 --> 00:08:50,340
 you have to see the second side of the verse.

178
00:08:50,340 --> 00:08:52,340
 In the Greek, it says something along the lines

179
00:08:52,340 --> 00:08:55,780
 of like this, because, so I'm not ashamed of the gospel

180
00:08:55,780 --> 00:09:00,780
 because it is the power of God for everyone in salvation

181
00:09:00,780 --> 00:09:03,140
 for everyone who believes.

182
00:09:03,140 --> 00:09:04,980
 Paul, once again, does something controversial.

183
00:09:04,980 --> 00:09:08,020
 In the first half, he chooses his Greek word, ashamed,

184
00:09:08,020 --> 00:09:09,580
 which connected to the culture.

185
00:09:09,580 --> 00:09:11,620
 He does the same sort of thing in the second half.

186
00:09:11,620 --> 00:09:13,620
 He takes this word power,

187
00:09:13,620 --> 00:09:16,580
 which was central to the Roman church

188
00:09:16,580 --> 00:09:18,940
 and the reality of that Roman culture.

189
00:09:18,940 --> 00:09:23,180
 And he says, you wanna know what true power is?

190
00:09:23,180 --> 00:09:26,460
 It is not what you have been told.

191
00:09:26,460 --> 00:09:29,660
 It is not what everything in the city is trying

192
00:09:29,660 --> 00:09:31,660
 and is designed to try to proclaim.

193
00:09:31,660 --> 00:09:34,780
 He's saying, here's what the true power is.

194
00:09:34,780 --> 00:09:37,380
 The gospel is true power.

195
00:09:37,380 --> 00:09:39,980
 And the reason why is because it turns

196
00:09:39,980 --> 00:09:44,700
 this whole honor shame system on its head.

197
00:09:44,700 --> 00:09:51,340
 See, Paul, he understood this was the gospel.

198
00:09:51,340 --> 00:09:52,580
 If he was standing right here,

199
00:09:52,580 --> 00:09:54,460
 he would tell you this is the gospel,

200
00:09:54,460 --> 00:09:59,460
 that God had such a heart for the broken world around him,

201
00:09:59,460 --> 00:10:03,820
 that he didn't consider being acquainted with that power

202
00:10:03,820 --> 00:10:06,180
 and that authority on high, something to be grasped,

203
00:10:06,180 --> 00:10:10,260
 but he humbled himself and he came here in this incarnation.

204
00:10:10,260 --> 00:10:12,660
 And through a place of humility and love,

205
00:10:12,660 --> 00:10:17,420
 he allowed himself to be crucified.

206
00:10:17,420 --> 00:10:19,900
 He allowed himself to experience

207
00:10:19,900 --> 00:10:24,900
 the worst public social shame that you could experience.

208
00:10:24,900 --> 00:10:29,940
 And the reason why he allowed himself to be shamed so much

209
00:10:29,940 --> 00:10:32,540
 was that because three days later,

210
00:10:32,540 --> 00:10:35,380
 God raised him from death to life.

211
00:10:35,380 --> 00:10:37,580
 And in raising him back into life,

212
00:10:37,580 --> 00:10:39,980
 God makes a statement over the world

213
00:10:39,980 --> 00:10:43,540
 that there is no amount of shame anymore

214
00:10:43,540 --> 00:10:46,700
 that can ever hold you back from the love of God.

215
00:10:48,220 --> 00:10:50,660
 So he's saying, and this is really theologically

216
00:10:50,660 --> 00:10:53,580
 quite beautiful how he's taking Greek and Roman culture

217
00:10:53,580 --> 00:10:55,540
 and he's actually flipping it 'cause he's saying

218
00:10:55,540 --> 00:10:59,380
 the thing that you think is the place of greatest shame

219
00:10:59,380 --> 00:11:02,460
 is actually the very thing that gives the greatest freedom.

220
00:11:02,460 --> 00:11:07,940
 In other words, true power is not being released

221
00:11:07,940 --> 00:11:10,220
 from shame and dishonor socially,

222
00:11:10,220 --> 00:11:13,560
 it's being released from shame and dishonor eternally.

223
00:11:13,560 --> 00:11:17,700
 That's what happens on the cross.

224
00:11:17,700 --> 00:11:19,500
 That's what Jesus does.

225
00:11:19,500 --> 00:11:23,060
 He stands in the gap and takes all of the shame of sin

226
00:11:23,060 --> 00:11:27,700
 on his shoulders, the dishonor of every sin ever committed,

227
00:11:27,700 --> 00:11:31,340
 he takes it upon himself and in raising to new life,

228
00:11:31,340 --> 00:11:35,940
 forgives that sin, is the one sacrifice that pays the price

229
00:11:35,940 --> 00:11:39,340
 so that no one else has to suffer anymore

230
00:11:39,340 --> 00:11:41,820
 under any shame, any dishonor,

231
00:11:41,820 --> 00:11:44,620
 that even in the worst of our sin,

232
00:11:44,620 --> 00:11:47,300
 we have a God who still loves.

233
00:11:47,300 --> 00:11:49,740
 We have a God who has set us free

234
00:11:49,740 --> 00:11:51,900
 and we have a God who's created a pathway

235
00:11:51,900 --> 00:11:56,900
 by which we can go from our shame to eternal glory in him.

236
00:11:56,900 --> 00:12:00,460
 So I am not ashamed of the gospel, Paul said,

237
00:12:00,460 --> 00:12:04,900
 because it is the very power to set you free

238
00:12:04,900 --> 00:12:08,180
 from the shame society is placing on you.

239
00:12:08,180 --> 00:12:16,260
 It's pretty cool because this enables the church in Rome

240
00:12:17,100 --> 00:12:19,780
 to begin to think about everything differently

241
00:12:19,780 --> 00:12:23,020
 and begin to go, everybody around us is suffering

242
00:12:23,020 --> 00:12:26,300
 with this system of honor and shame, honor and shame.

243
00:12:26,300 --> 00:12:29,580
 Everybody's so consumed by how they think of themselves

244
00:12:29,580 --> 00:12:32,700
 and how they think of others and they're stressed out,

245
00:12:32,700 --> 00:12:35,460
 they're anxious, there's all this stuff going on

246
00:12:35,460 --> 00:12:39,860
 and we have the very message that sets them free from that.

247
00:12:39,860 --> 00:12:43,500
 But when we are ashamed of the gospel,

248
00:12:43,500 --> 00:12:46,980
 we keep the very message that can set them free

249
00:12:46,980 --> 00:12:49,860
 simply to ourselves.

250
00:12:49,860 --> 00:12:54,060
 If I was to summarize these two sides

251
00:12:54,060 --> 00:12:55,860
 of this really profound verse,

252
00:12:55,860 --> 00:12:58,460
 I would summarize it like this.

253
00:12:58,460 --> 00:13:01,620
 By emphasizing the gospel's divine power,

254
00:13:01,620 --> 00:13:03,660
 Paul is countering the perceived shame

255
00:13:03,660 --> 00:13:07,100
 of a crucified Messiah and boldly challenging

256
00:13:07,100 --> 00:13:09,340
 the honor-shame system of his day,

257
00:13:09,340 --> 00:13:12,380
 prioritizing, notice this, divine approval

258
00:13:12,380 --> 00:13:15,900
 over cultural acceptance, that is public faith.

259
00:13:15,900 --> 00:13:20,820
 Where we're gonna prioritize divine approval

260
00:13:20,820 --> 00:13:24,180
 over cultural acceptance.

261
00:13:24,180 --> 00:13:29,900
 It should be not lost on us that here in Hong Kong,

262
00:13:29,900 --> 00:13:33,940
 we're still living in an honor-shame society, are we not?

263
00:13:33,940 --> 00:13:37,420
 I mean, the idea of the loss of face

264
00:13:37,420 --> 00:13:40,500
 is so embedded into our culture here in Hong Kong

265
00:13:40,500 --> 00:13:43,460
 and perhaps you've experienced what it's like to lose face

266
00:13:43,460 --> 00:13:45,980
 or perhaps someone in your family has experienced that

267
00:13:45,980 --> 00:13:49,220
 and you know what that social pull can be like,

268
00:13:49,220 --> 00:13:53,940
 you know the brokenness of a honor-shame culture and society.

269
00:13:53,940 --> 00:13:56,140
 So perhaps now more than ever,

270
00:13:56,140 --> 00:13:58,540
 this phrase that Paul writes to the church in Rome

271
00:13:58,540 --> 00:14:00,700
 that was important for them 2000 years ago

272
00:14:00,700 --> 00:14:03,620
 is even more important for the church of Hong Kong today

273
00:14:03,620 --> 00:14:06,700
 and perhaps it should be preached in every pulpit

274
00:14:06,700 --> 00:14:08,300
 of every church in this city.

275
00:14:08,300 --> 00:14:11,380
 We are not ashamed of the gospel,

276
00:14:11,380 --> 00:14:14,540
 for it is the power of God for salvation

277
00:14:14,540 --> 00:14:16,620
 for all who believe.

278
00:14:16,620 --> 00:14:23,060
 The challenge we have though,

279
00:14:23,060 --> 00:14:27,900
 is that even in the desire to want to proclaim that,

280
00:14:27,900 --> 00:14:29,820
 we recognize the fear inside of us.

281
00:14:29,820 --> 00:14:32,060
 We recognize the persecution,

282
00:14:32,060 --> 00:14:35,340
 we recognize the weight and the heaviness of a society

283
00:14:35,340 --> 00:14:39,100
 that can be so often against the very message that we hold.

284
00:14:39,100 --> 00:14:41,620
 We worry about the loss of face,

285
00:14:41,620 --> 00:14:43,980
 we worry about the social impact,

286
00:14:43,980 --> 00:14:47,420
 we worry about our jobs.

287
00:14:47,420 --> 00:14:48,780
 And all of those things have weight

288
00:14:48,780 --> 00:14:52,020
 and all those things need to be held in balance with this

289
00:14:52,020 --> 00:14:55,220
 but ultimately Paul writes to a church and says,

290
00:14:55,220 --> 00:14:58,380
 "Do not think that you are shamed by this gospel,

291
00:14:58,380 --> 00:15:01,060
 "in fact, remember that it is the very gospel

292
00:15:01,060 --> 00:15:02,700
 "that frees you from that shame."

293
00:15:04,060 --> 00:15:06,300
 And what a message of great hope that can be

294
00:15:06,300 --> 00:15:07,980
 for here in Hong Kong today

295
00:15:07,980 --> 00:15:10,100
 but we have to realize that that hope

296
00:15:10,100 --> 00:15:13,460
 is not a default reality.

297
00:15:13,460 --> 00:15:14,900
 What I mean by that is that,

298
00:15:14,900 --> 00:15:18,180
 that message has to go out.

299
00:15:18,180 --> 00:15:19,580
 If all of it ever is,

300
00:15:19,580 --> 00:15:21,940
 is kept within the hearts and the lives

301
00:15:21,940 --> 00:15:23,860
 of fiery Christians on a Sunday

302
00:15:23,860 --> 00:15:25,740
 who raised their hands and sing loudly

303
00:15:25,740 --> 00:15:28,740
 but never actually works out into their public sphere

304
00:15:28,740 --> 00:15:31,140
 of their influence in the world,

305
00:15:31,140 --> 00:15:33,260
 then the very gift that God has given us

306
00:15:33,260 --> 00:15:35,260
 to bring the hope to those that need it the most

307
00:15:35,260 --> 00:15:38,540
 never gets heard, we need to preach it.

308
00:15:38,540 --> 00:15:43,100
 Paul actually just a few chapters later in chapter 10,

309
00:15:43,100 --> 00:15:44,500
 he says that exact thing.

310
00:15:44,500 --> 00:15:46,420
 Let me read this to you in chapter 10,

311
00:15:46,420 --> 00:15:47,860
 starting in verse 14.

312
00:15:47,860 --> 00:15:50,460
 He said, "How then can they call on the one

313
00:15:50,460 --> 00:15:52,420
 "that they have not believed in?

314
00:15:52,420 --> 00:15:54,260
 "And how can they believe in the one

315
00:15:54,260 --> 00:15:56,020
 "whom they have not heard?

316
00:15:56,020 --> 00:16:00,620
 "And how can they hear without someone preaching to them?"

317
00:16:00,620 --> 00:16:01,900
 And so Paul says, look,

318
00:16:01,900 --> 00:16:03,940
 it's not just gonna be a default reality

319
00:16:03,940 --> 00:16:05,660
 that people realize, oh, there's a God out there

320
00:16:05,660 --> 00:16:07,380
 who has forgiven me of my shame and my brokenness

321
00:16:07,380 --> 00:16:09,660
 and my sin and I can have relations with him and new life.

322
00:16:09,660 --> 00:16:11,420
 No, this needs to be communicated.

323
00:16:11,420 --> 00:16:12,700
 It needs to be lived.

324
00:16:12,700 --> 00:16:13,940
 It needs to be preached.

325
00:16:13,940 --> 00:16:16,300
 It's one thing to believe

326
00:16:16,300 --> 00:16:18,500
 that you are not ashamed of the gospel

327
00:16:18,500 --> 00:16:21,060
 or to even believe that it is the power of God

328
00:16:21,060 --> 00:16:22,380
 to bring salvation to the world,

329
00:16:22,380 --> 00:16:25,420
 but it's a whole other thing to actually then preach it,

330
00:16:25,420 --> 00:16:28,500
 to actually then live it,

331
00:16:28,500 --> 00:16:30,540
 to actually then want to proclaim it,

332
00:16:30,540 --> 00:16:34,060
 want to reveal it in whatever creative, bold,

333
00:16:34,060 --> 00:16:38,460
 beautiful ways that your life might be created to do that.

334
00:16:38,460 --> 00:16:40,460
 That's a whole another thing.

335
00:16:40,460 --> 00:16:42,500
 I'm challenged to say it this way.

336
00:16:42,500 --> 00:16:45,620
 We are the greatest of hypocrites.

337
00:16:45,620 --> 00:16:48,460
 If here's what, we're the greatest hypocrites in the world

338
00:16:48,460 --> 00:16:51,340
 if on the one hand, we have this idea

339
00:16:51,340 --> 00:16:53,260
 that we are not ashamed of the gospel,

340
00:16:53,260 --> 00:16:56,900
 but on the other hand, we still keep it private.

341
00:16:56,900 --> 00:16:57,900
 That's hypocritical.

342
00:16:58,820 --> 00:17:00,300
 We should be ashamed by that.

343
00:17:00,300 --> 00:17:02,380
 I mean, we shouldn't say,

344
00:17:02,380 --> 00:17:04,100
 "Hey, I'm not ashamed of the gospel,"

345
00:17:04,100 --> 00:17:06,180
 and then like never tell anyone about it.

346
00:17:06,180 --> 00:17:08,460
 Those two things don't work together.

347
00:17:08,460 --> 00:17:11,300
 And so Paul is saying,

348
00:17:11,300 --> 00:17:13,740
 "Look, the first thing you have to understand,

349
00:17:13,740 --> 00:17:16,020
 we are not ashamed by this gospel,

350
00:17:16,020 --> 00:17:19,900
 for it is the power of God for salvation

351
00:17:19,900 --> 00:17:21,940
 for all who believe.

352
00:17:21,940 --> 00:17:25,140
 The very thing that was the instrument of shame

353
00:17:25,140 --> 00:17:28,500
 has become the very thing that's broken shame."

354
00:17:29,500 --> 00:17:30,540
 That's good news.

355
00:17:30,540 --> 00:17:33,180
 That's very, very good news.

356
00:17:33,180 --> 00:17:36,820
 And that's good news for Hong Kong at a time

357
00:17:36,820 --> 00:17:40,300
 when I think Hong Kong needs some good news.

358
00:17:40,300 --> 00:17:42,380
 I want you to have a look at this table behind me.

359
00:17:42,380 --> 00:17:44,580
 This is the number of Christians in Hong Kong

360
00:17:44,580 --> 00:17:45,700
 over the last decade.

361
00:17:45,700 --> 00:17:49,180
 So 2015 through to 2025.

362
00:17:49,180 --> 00:17:51,660
 Now, there's some encouragement in this graph

363
00:17:51,660 --> 00:17:53,620
 as you can probably see.

364
00:17:53,620 --> 00:17:54,860
 Back 10 years ago,

365
00:17:54,860 --> 00:17:57,060
 we had about a million Christians in Hong Kong,

366
00:17:57,060 --> 00:17:58,380
 Protestant and Catholic,

367
00:17:58,380 --> 00:18:02,340
 which was about 13.9% of the population at that time.

368
00:18:02,340 --> 00:18:03,460
 Today in 2025,

369
00:18:03,460 --> 00:18:07,020
 we have roughly about 1.4 million Protestants and Catholics

370
00:18:07,020 --> 00:18:08,060
 in Hong Kong,

371
00:18:08,060 --> 00:18:12,300
 which comes to about 19% of the population today.

372
00:18:12,300 --> 00:18:13,740
 So actually in the last decade,

373
00:18:13,740 --> 00:18:17,540
 Christianity in our city has grown by 40%.

374
00:18:17,540 --> 00:18:18,980
 That's pretty good news.

375
00:18:18,980 --> 00:18:20,060
 I don't think that's great news,

376
00:18:20,060 --> 00:18:21,700
 but that's pretty good news, right?

377
00:18:21,700 --> 00:18:22,940
 Like 40% is decent.

378
00:18:22,940 --> 00:18:24,460
 We're heading in the right direction.

379
00:18:24,460 --> 00:18:26,380
 You'll notice that the population of Hong Kong

380
00:18:26,380 --> 00:18:27,420
 Christian is going

381
00:18:27,420 --> 00:18:29,020
 and the population of Hong Kong is going down.

382
00:18:29,020 --> 00:18:29,980
 We're going up, they're going down.

383
00:18:29,980 --> 00:18:31,700
 I don't know what's going on there.

384
00:18:31,700 --> 00:18:34,620
 One day we'll meet, you know, in the middle.

385
00:18:34,620 --> 00:18:37,300
 But there's some good news in that graph.

386
00:18:37,300 --> 00:18:39,260
 But here's the statistic of that graph

387
00:18:39,260 --> 00:18:40,980
 that moves me the most.

388
00:18:40,980 --> 00:18:43,060
 There's still 80% of the people of our city

389
00:18:43,060 --> 00:18:44,180
 that don't know Jesus.

390
00:18:44,180 --> 00:18:49,900
 80% when the church has been in Hong Kong for 100 years.

391
00:18:49,900 --> 00:18:52,060
 When the church has been in our city for 100 years

392
00:18:52,060 --> 00:18:54,420
 and there's still 80% of the people in the city

393
00:18:54,420 --> 00:18:57,740
 that don't profess Jesus as their Lord and Savior,

394
00:18:57,740 --> 00:18:59,300
 we have to be honest with ourselves

395
00:18:59,300 --> 00:19:02,060
 and say, are we actually ashamed of the gospel?

396
00:19:02,060 --> 00:19:09,860
 Six years ago, God lit a fire under us here at the Vine

397
00:19:09,860 --> 00:19:13,620
 when it comes to this idea of sharing the gospel

398
00:19:13,620 --> 00:19:15,980
 or living or being the gospel more in our city.

399
00:19:15,980 --> 00:19:19,620
 He challenged us in how we view what it is to do church,

400
00:19:19,620 --> 00:19:21,300
 to be church, to have church.

401
00:19:21,300 --> 00:19:22,900
 And he challenged us that we need to start

402
00:19:22,900 --> 00:19:25,340
 thinking of church differently from one building

403
00:19:25,340 --> 00:19:30,060
 in one static location to church being the people of God

404
00:19:30,060 --> 00:19:32,300
 who spread out in their spheres of influence

405
00:19:32,300 --> 00:19:35,180
 around their city a little bit like a river

406
00:19:35,180 --> 00:19:37,500
 that flows through the city.

407
00:19:37,500 --> 00:19:39,820
 So you've probably heard us talk about the river model

408
00:19:39,820 --> 00:19:41,420
 over the last six years.

409
00:19:41,420 --> 00:19:44,900
 This beautiful idea that we can take the gospel

410
00:19:44,900 --> 00:19:47,180
 into all of our spheres of influence,

411
00:19:47,180 --> 00:19:51,100
 like that river watering every part of our city

412
00:19:51,100 --> 00:19:52,780
 for the glory of God.

413
00:19:52,780 --> 00:19:56,500
 It's a beautiful, bold, courageous vision

414
00:19:56,500 --> 00:20:00,820
 that can only happen if God stirs something within us

415
00:20:00,820 --> 00:20:01,860
 and in our hearts.

416
00:20:01,860 --> 00:20:04,900
 Because of this vision six years ago,

417
00:20:04,900 --> 00:20:06,580
 we began to think and pray as a leadership

418
00:20:06,580 --> 00:20:08,020
 around church planting.

419
00:20:08,020 --> 00:20:11,100
 'Cause when God says, hey, this is how I want you to be,

420
00:20:11,100 --> 00:20:13,580
 a river flowing in the city, we began to think,

421
00:20:13,580 --> 00:20:16,020
 well, we need to be flowing in the city.

422
00:20:16,020 --> 00:20:17,500
 And that means in our workplaces

423
00:20:17,500 --> 00:20:18,420
 and it means that the people,

424
00:20:18,420 --> 00:20:20,540
 but it also means that we need to express

425
00:20:20,540 --> 00:20:23,700
 ourselves across the city in different ways.

426
00:20:23,700 --> 00:20:25,340
 And you'll know three years ago,

427
00:20:25,340 --> 00:20:27,180
 we started our first church plant.

428
00:20:27,180 --> 00:20:31,540
 We planted in Yulong and Tim and Ivan as leaders there,

429
00:20:31,540 --> 00:20:34,180
 and the other staff there have done a tremendous job

430
00:20:34,180 --> 00:20:35,740
 over the last three years.

431
00:20:35,740 --> 00:20:37,260
 There's probably around about 300 people

432
00:20:37,260 --> 00:20:40,420
 that meet regularly on a Sunday in Yulong.

433
00:20:40,420 --> 00:20:42,780
 We have service in Cantonese and in English.

434
00:20:42,780 --> 00:20:45,420
 And a lot of those 300 people are new believers.

435
00:20:45,420 --> 00:20:47,020
 People have come to Christ

436
00:20:47,020 --> 00:20:48,420
 because we planted something there.

437
00:20:48,420 --> 00:20:49,940
 We've reached out with the gospel.

438
00:20:49,940 --> 00:20:51,980
 We've believed that we're not gonna be ashamed of it

439
00:20:51,980 --> 00:20:53,900
 and that we're gonna bring an expression of it

440
00:20:53,900 --> 00:20:57,780
 to a cultural group of people that need it most.

441
00:20:57,780 --> 00:20:59,300
 Well, today, I'm really excited

442
00:20:59,300 --> 00:21:02,020
 that we're making another big announcement.

443
00:21:02,020 --> 00:21:03,700
 This is gonna be a Sunday where you're gonna look back

444
00:21:03,700 --> 00:21:07,060
 in a few years' time and go, I was there that day.

445
00:21:07,060 --> 00:21:09,660
 And to help make that big announcement,

446
00:21:09,660 --> 00:21:12,420
 I'm really excited to invite to the stage

447
00:21:12,420 --> 00:21:14,460
 two people that have been very central

448
00:21:14,460 --> 00:21:16,700
 to the life and growth and development of the Vine

449
00:21:16,700 --> 00:21:18,740
 over the last 18 years.

450
00:21:18,740 --> 00:21:20,700
 They've held staff roles here.

451
00:21:20,700 --> 00:21:23,740
 They've been volunteers within our ministry.

452
00:21:23,740 --> 00:21:24,980
 But they have a heart.

453
00:21:24,980 --> 00:21:28,420
 I think they're like the pools of the pool to Rome.

454
00:21:28,420 --> 00:21:29,340
 They are like them.

455
00:21:29,340 --> 00:21:31,620
 They're like pool to Hong Kong in this time.

456
00:21:31,620 --> 00:21:33,700
 I know for 100% certainty

457
00:21:33,700 --> 00:21:35,340
 that they are not ashamed of the gospel.

458
00:21:35,340 --> 00:21:36,660
 So to help us make this announcement,

459
00:21:36,660 --> 00:21:37,780
 can you put your hands together

460
00:21:37,780 --> 00:21:39,500
 as we invite Sydney and Vivian Yip?

461
00:21:39,500 --> 00:21:42,660
 (audience applauding)

462
00:21:42,660 --> 00:21:45,820
 (audience applauding)

463
00:21:45,820 --> 00:21:51,660
 - Good morning, Church.

464
00:21:51,660 --> 00:21:54,500
 - Well, thank you, Andrew.

465
00:21:54,500 --> 00:21:57,660
 Well, we are going to share some of our stories

466
00:21:57,660 --> 00:22:00,260
 and hope that they find resonance in you

467
00:22:00,260 --> 00:22:03,340
 before we do the announcement part of it.

468
00:22:03,340 --> 00:22:06,620
 My name is Sydney and this is Vivian.

469
00:22:06,620 --> 00:22:12,180
 We just celebrated our 34th wedding anniversary.

470
00:22:12,180 --> 00:22:15,340
 (audience applauding)

471
00:22:15,340 --> 00:22:20,020
 We've been in the Vine community for the past 18 years.

472
00:22:20,020 --> 00:22:23,900
 I've the privilege to serve in the eldership for nine years,

473
00:22:23,900 --> 00:22:27,860
 including five years as chairman of the board.

474
00:22:27,860 --> 00:22:31,740
 But I'd like to rewind it to 50 years ago,

475
00:22:31,740 --> 00:22:35,580
 okay, when I entered into my secondary school.

476
00:22:35,580 --> 00:22:40,580
 And the name of the secondary school is Yinghua College,

477
00:22:40,700 --> 00:22:45,300
 which literally means Anglo-Chinese school,

478
00:22:45,300 --> 00:22:46,460
 Yinghua, Siyun.

479
00:22:46,460 --> 00:22:50,940
 Now, on that very first day, when I started,

480
00:22:50,940 --> 00:22:53,900
 I literally cried my eyes out

481
00:22:53,900 --> 00:22:56,820
 because that was my third choice of school.

482
00:22:56,820 --> 00:22:59,980
 But God had a greater plan.

483
00:22:59,980 --> 00:23:03,180
 I only subsequently knew that Yinghua

484
00:23:03,180 --> 00:23:07,220
 was first founded in 1818,

485
00:23:07,220 --> 00:23:08,940
 more than 200 years ago,

486
00:23:08,940 --> 00:23:12,140
 by the London Missionary Society.

487
00:23:12,140 --> 00:23:16,740
 Their vision was to educate Chinese students,

488
00:23:16,740 --> 00:23:20,940
 teaching literacy, morals, and Christian values.

489
00:23:20,940 --> 00:23:25,940
 But most of all, they would want them to become agents

490
00:23:25,940 --> 00:23:28,380
 to bring the gospel to China.

491
00:23:28,380 --> 00:23:35,180
 Now, that seed of vision continued for over 200 years.

492
00:23:35,180 --> 00:23:39,580
 And I'm always amazed how more than half of my classmates

493
00:23:39,580 --> 00:23:42,760
 come to faith during our school years,

494
00:23:42,760 --> 00:23:45,860
 many of whom became pastors, elders,

495
00:23:45,860 --> 00:23:48,100
 leaders in Christian NGOs,

496
00:23:48,100 --> 00:23:52,260
 or serving in their own right in unique manners.

497
00:23:52,260 --> 00:23:55,700
 I am also one of the first.

498
00:23:55,700 --> 00:23:57,380
 Though somehow along the way,

499
00:23:57,380 --> 00:23:59,860
 I backslid in my faith commitments,

500
00:23:59,860 --> 00:24:02,460
 I went on to pursue some of my own dreams

501
00:24:02,460 --> 00:24:06,220
 and drifted away from faith for more than 15 years.

502
00:24:06,220 --> 00:24:07,700
 But God is gracious.

503
00:24:07,700 --> 00:24:11,540
 As if in Genesis, Joseph say,

504
00:24:11,540 --> 00:24:13,020
 "Well, you intended to,

505
00:24:13,020 --> 00:24:16,120
 "well, I intended to pursue my own dreams,

506
00:24:16,120 --> 00:24:18,960
 "but God intended it for good,

507
00:24:18,960 --> 00:24:21,580
 "to accomplish what is now being done,

508
00:24:21,580 --> 00:24:24,940
 "the saving of many lives."

509
00:24:24,940 --> 00:24:26,780
 So it was actually some time down the road

510
00:24:26,780 --> 00:24:28,700
 when we moved over to Singapore

511
00:24:28,700 --> 00:24:32,380
 that my passion to serve Him reignited.

512
00:24:32,380 --> 00:24:35,600
 So on one of the weekends,

513
00:24:35,600 --> 00:24:40,340
 while I was working as a medical profession in Singapore,

514
00:24:40,340 --> 00:24:43,880
 one of my patients left into a sudden coma.

515
00:24:43,880 --> 00:24:46,180
 So his wife was devastated.

516
00:24:46,180 --> 00:24:48,860
 I want to bring some comfort to her,

517
00:24:48,860 --> 00:24:51,820
 but she was a Mandarin speaker.

518
00:24:51,820 --> 00:24:54,020
 So I called up my church pastors,

519
00:24:54,020 --> 00:24:56,380
 as usual, as many of you would have done.

520
00:24:56,380 --> 00:24:59,280
 But on a Sunday or Saturday, I can't remember exactly,

521
00:24:59,280 --> 00:25:01,400
 no one was really available.

522
00:25:01,400 --> 00:25:04,900
 So I was tasked by the leader that,

523
00:25:04,900 --> 00:25:07,380
 "Well, why not go and reach out,

524
00:25:07,380 --> 00:25:10,740
 "share comfort and good news with her?"

525
00:25:10,740 --> 00:25:14,380
 So the backdrop is we really came

526
00:25:14,380 --> 00:25:16,740
 from an English-speaking congregation,

527
00:25:16,740 --> 00:25:20,980
 but I record, well, that some time ago,

528
00:25:20,980 --> 00:25:23,620
 that was in the '70s,

529
00:25:23,620 --> 00:25:26,640
 we were taught Mandarin in Yinghua College.

530
00:25:26,640 --> 00:25:28,140
 So I pick up some of those

531
00:25:28,140 --> 00:25:30,260
 and shared a word of encouragement.

532
00:25:31,280 --> 00:25:34,200
 Now, the important matter was,

533
00:25:34,200 --> 00:25:40,940
 well, I realized that God could be using me

534
00:25:40,940 --> 00:25:44,280
 to reach out to Chinese-speaking people.

535
00:25:44,280 --> 00:25:47,860
 Now, as we shared earlier on,

536
00:25:47,860 --> 00:25:49,460
 we actually returned to Hong Kong

537
00:25:49,460 --> 00:25:52,420
 and joined Divine for the past two decades.

538
00:25:52,420 --> 00:25:53,380
 Actually, through the years,

539
00:25:53,380 --> 00:25:57,180
 we saw God's hands working in this church,

540
00:25:57,180 --> 00:25:59,100
 building something really beautiful,

541
00:25:59,100 --> 00:26:03,200
 especially in the reaching out to Chinese speakers.

542
00:26:03,200 --> 00:26:06,160
 Looking back, I can see the seed planted in me

543
00:26:06,160 --> 00:26:09,880
 50 years ago is continuing to grow,

544
00:26:09,880 --> 00:26:14,100
 and I want to be faithful to God and His calling.

545
00:26:14,100 --> 00:26:19,340
 >> For me, my journey began in Singapore

546
00:26:19,340 --> 00:26:22,040
 more than 25 years ago.

547
00:26:22,040 --> 00:26:25,260
 My family moved there when I was in mid-30s,

548
00:26:25,260 --> 00:26:28,840
 and hardly knew anyone there.

549
00:26:28,840 --> 00:26:30,180
 One day at the pool,

550
00:26:30,180 --> 00:26:33,360
 while our kids were in the swimming class,

551
00:26:33,360 --> 00:26:36,280
 another mom began chatting with me,

552
00:26:36,280 --> 00:26:37,760
 and we quickly connected.

553
00:26:37,760 --> 00:26:41,860
 Through her friendship and outreach,

554
00:26:41,860 --> 00:26:44,700
 I was welcomed into her home church,

555
00:26:44,700 --> 00:26:48,380
 and that eventually became my community.

556
00:26:48,380 --> 00:26:52,760
 I was not treated as a foreigner or an outsider.

557
00:26:52,760 --> 00:26:55,080
 I was accepted and loved,

558
00:26:55,080 --> 00:26:59,220
 and there, I accepted Christ as my own savior.

559
00:26:59,220 --> 00:27:02,440
 Our marriage grew stronger,

560
00:27:02,440 --> 00:27:06,560
 and our family become closer.

561
00:27:06,560 --> 00:27:10,480
 We opened our home for small groups,

562
00:27:10,480 --> 00:27:13,580
 and we were tremendously blessed,

563
00:27:13,580 --> 00:27:15,080
 and then we let small group,

564
00:27:15,080 --> 00:27:19,540
 including family group with children ministry.

565
00:27:19,540 --> 00:27:24,540
 That is our family group that in Singapore years ago.

566
00:27:25,540 --> 00:27:28,900
 Yeah, and that, yeah,

567
00:27:28,900 --> 00:27:32,220
 our lives were indeed transformed.

568
00:27:32,220 --> 00:27:35,360
 I also got involved in the inner healing

569
00:27:35,360 --> 00:27:36,500
 and deliverance ministry,

570
00:27:36,500 --> 00:27:40,280
 as well as the pastoral care ministry.

571
00:27:40,280 --> 00:27:42,220
 Over these 10 years,

572
00:27:42,220 --> 00:27:46,600
 we witnessed our home church has planted

573
00:27:46,600 --> 00:27:48,980
 at least two more churches.

574
00:27:48,980 --> 00:27:52,260
 When my family moved back from Singapore,

575
00:27:52,260 --> 00:27:56,140
 I finished my theological studies in Hong Kong,

576
00:27:56,140 --> 00:27:58,980
 but even before I knew exactly

577
00:27:58,980 --> 00:28:02,380
 what God wanted me to do and serve,

578
00:28:02,380 --> 00:28:07,940
 God was really and already leading me.

579
00:28:07,940 --> 00:28:09,580
 He led us to the vine,

580
00:28:09,580 --> 00:28:13,740
 and I joined the pastoral staff team in 2014.

581
00:28:13,740 --> 00:28:17,260
 Over the years, I am honored being part

582
00:28:17,260 --> 00:28:21,400
 of this wonderful senior leadership team,

583
00:28:21,400 --> 00:28:25,760
 and I am passionate to lead the Chinese ministry,

584
00:28:25,760 --> 00:28:29,020
 both the Cantonese and the Mandarin communities,

585
00:28:29,020 --> 00:28:32,900
 and more recently, leading the restoration ministry.

586
00:28:32,900 --> 00:28:39,060
 But I would like to flash back in 2014

587
00:28:39,060 --> 00:28:42,900
 at the English and Cantonese Alva Retreat

588
00:28:42,900 --> 00:28:45,620
 in the West Ark of Ma Wan.

589
00:28:45,620 --> 00:28:48,860
 God gave me a vision during worship.

590
00:28:50,460 --> 00:28:54,720
 I saw dazzling lights spread across the land,

591
00:28:54,720 --> 00:28:58,620
 shining outward in all directions.

592
00:28:58,620 --> 00:29:01,920
 I did not fully understand them,

593
00:29:01,920 --> 00:29:05,060
 but my heart sensed it was the call

594
00:29:05,060 --> 00:29:09,320
 to reach further the Chinese community.

595
00:29:09,320 --> 00:29:12,860
 What we began as a home group of 20

596
00:29:12,860 --> 00:29:16,800
 has grown into a vibrant Chinese ministry,

597
00:29:16,800 --> 00:29:19,980
 and you will see here is a picture

598
00:29:19,980 --> 00:29:24,240
 of our Cantonese community back in 2018.

599
00:29:24,240 --> 00:29:30,640
 And now today, my heart still believes God is saying,

600
00:29:30,640 --> 00:29:33,260
 "There is more to come,"

601
00:29:33,260 --> 00:29:36,060
 and I want to avail myself to love the people

602
00:29:36,060 --> 00:29:39,240
 that God put into our lives.

603
00:29:39,240 --> 00:29:40,880
 - So what is this more?

604
00:29:40,880 --> 00:29:45,740
 Divine has embraced the Reformation for six, seven years,

605
00:29:45,740 --> 00:29:49,100
 and I pray that this will continue to inspire us

606
00:29:49,100 --> 00:29:52,620
 to see that we can be part of something even bigger,

607
00:29:52,620 --> 00:29:54,420
 which is still unfolding.

608
00:29:54,420 --> 00:29:59,000
 Today, we are excited to announce that Vivian and I,

609
00:29:59,000 --> 00:30:02,460
 together with the leadership of Divine,

610
00:30:02,460 --> 00:30:05,500
 are sensing a call for us to move out

611
00:30:05,500 --> 00:30:10,500
 and plant a fresh kind of missional outreach fine church

612
00:30:10,500 --> 00:30:14,980
 in the North Metropolis area of Hong Kong.

613
00:30:17,020 --> 00:30:20,340
 Now, the call of this new River Initiative is distinct.

614
00:30:20,340 --> 00:30:23,660
 It would be sharing the love of Christ

615
00:30:23,660 --> 00:30:28,280
 with Chinese speakers, Mandarin and Cantonese included,

616
00:30:28,280 --> 00:30:31,620
 in a way that encourage real spiritual growth

617
00:30:31,620 --> 00:30:35,740
 and builds loving, Christ-centered communities

618
00:30:35,740 --> 00:30:37,580
 without walls.

619
00:30:37,580 --> 00:30:40,700
 Our mission is to create a network

620
00:30:40,700 --> 00:30:43,260
 of these caring communities

621
00:30:43,260 --> 00:30:47,000
 woven throughout the North Metropolis of Hong Kong.

622
00:30:47,000 --> 00:30:51,060
 And we hope and we dream

623
00:30:51,060 --> 00:30:55,900
 that there will be planting church, planting churches.

624
00:30:55,900 --> 00:30:57,980
 So they aren't just churches in buildings,

625
00:30:57,980 --> 00:31:02,500
 they are churches in homes, workplaces, and neighborhoods,

626
00:31:02,500 --> 00:31:06,460
 everywhere people gather and live their daily lives.

627
00:31:06,460 --> 00:31:07,740
 And here's the real beauty.

628
00:31:07,740 --> 00:31:11,620
 As we plant new churches and communities,

629
00:31:11,620 --> 00:31:13,340
 they will in turn plant more.

630
00:31:13,340 --> 00:31:16,300
 And this multiplication will help us establish

631
00:31:16,300 --> 00:31:21,300
 a sustainable, vibrant gospel presence across the region.

632
00:31:21,300 --> 00:31:24,900
 It's not just about maintaining what's here.

633
00:31:24,900 --> 00:31:27,940
 It's about growing and spreading out

634
00:31:27,940 --> 00:31:31,000
 so that we may reach more lives for Jesus.

635
00:31:31,000 --> 00:31:36,940
 Even in John 15, it is read this way.

636
00:31:36,940 --> 00:31:40,960
 "Every branch that does bear fruit, he prunes.

637
00:31:41,800 --> 00:31:46,800
 "He prunes so that it may be even more fruitful."

638
00:31:46,800 --> 00:31:49,840
 And we yearn to be even more fruitful.

639
00:31:49,840 --> 00:31:53,040
 But then why focus on the North Metropolis?

640
00:31:53,040 --> 00:31:54,440
 So for obvious reasons,

641
00:31:54,440 --> 00:31:58,720
 it is one of the Hong Kong's fastest growing areas.

642
00:31:58,720 --> 00:32:01,320
 North Metropolis actually include area

643
00:32:01,320 --> 00:32:05,160
 beyond Shaanxi, Fanning, Yunnan, but also Tianshui,

644
00:32:05,160 --> 00:32:06,800
 and all the new zones in between,

645
00:32:06,800 --> 00:32:09,320
 including Kuchong, Shantin.

646
00:32:09,320 --> 00:32:10,600
 And over the next decade,

647
00:32:10,600 --> 00:32:14,640
 more than one million new residents will move in,

648
00:32:14,640 --> 00:32:19,120
 bringing the total population over there to 2.5 million.

649
00:32:19,120 --> 00:32:22,320
 Many will be new families, professionals,

650
00:32:22,320 --> 00:32:26,720
 people from Hong Kong who are relocated

651
00:32:26,720 --> 00:32:28,360
 from the original residence,

652
00:32:28,360 --> 00:32:30,880
 and also new residents from mainland China.

653
00:32:30,880 --> 00:32:33,920
 Now while some local churches in Hong Kong

654
00:32:33,920 --> 00:32:37,600
 are beginning to venture into this new area,

655
00:32:37,600 --> 00:32:41,280
 the overall landscape is that the people

656
00:32:41,280 --> 00:32:44,680
 are still underserved by churches.

657
00:32:44,680 --> 00:32:47,200
 Some places are instead blank slates.

658
00:32:47,200 --> 00:32:49,480
 And what an opportunity for the gospel

659
00:32:49,480 --> 00:32:52,340
 to take root and flourish.

660
00:32:52,340 --> 00:32:55,480
 - Yes, what excites me most are the people,

661
00:32:55,480 --> 00:32:58,680
 new neighbors, new families,

662
00:32:58,680 --> 00:33:01,380
 and who do not yet know Jesus.

663
00:33:01,380 --> 00:33:04,440
 Yeah, but Jesus loves them regardless,

664
00:33:04,440 --> 00:33:07,200
 no less than how He loves us.

665
00:33:08,080 --> 00:33:11,200
 God is inviting us to go to them,

666
00:33:11,200 --> 00:33:14,800
 to be His hands and feet in this new area,

667
00:33:14,800 --> 00:33:16,400
 Northern Metropolis.

668
00:33:16,400 --> 00:33:21,160
 Malachi 4, 5, and 6,

669
00:33:21,160 --> 00:33:24,080
 "See, I will send the prophet Elijah to you

670
00:33:24,080 --> 00:33:27,560
 "before that great and dreadful day of the Lord comes.

671
00:33:27,560 --> 00:33:31,560
 "He will turn the hearts of the parents to their children,

672
00:33:31,560 --> 00:33:35,040
 "and the hearts of the children to their parents."

673
00:33:35,360 --> 00:33:36,920
 At Divine Restoration,

674
00:33:36,920 --> 00:33:40,680
 we have heard many powerful testimonies

675
00:33:40,680 --> 00:33:43,520
 from participants in their courses.

676
00:33:43,520 --> 00:33:47,760
 Not only did they experience their personal heart healing,

677
00:33:47,760 --> 00:33:51,380
 but also the restoration of broken relationships.

678
00:33:51,380 --> 00:33:55,200
 Reconciliation is still happening in homes

679
00:33:55,200 --> 00:34:00,200
 between spouses, between parents and the children.

680
00:34:00,200 --> 00:34:05,140
 God is truly at work turning hearts back to Him,

681
00:34:05,140 --> 00:34:06,800
 and also to one another.

682
00:34:06,800 --> 00:34:11,080
 Let's see, Mark 4, 35.

683
00:34:11,080 --> 00:34:13,860
 "Let us go over to the other side.

684
00:34:13,860 --> 00:34:17,360
 "Despite the initial success and all reasons to stay,

685
00:34:17,360 --> 00:34:22,360
 "Jesus called His disciples to venture into new territories

686
00:34:22,360 --> 00:34:27,940
 "and potentially hostile ministry grounds.

687
00:34:27,940 --> 00:34:32,900
 "Likewise, our calling is to cross over,

688
00:34:32,900 --> 00:34:37,480
 "go further and step into this new uncharted,

689
00:34:37,480 --> 00:34:42,480
 "because many lives are waiting to encounter Jesus,

690
00:34:42,480 --> 00:34:45,820
 "His presence, His love, His hope."

691
00:34:45,820 --> 00:34:51,900
 - Do we dare to believe that God is indeed leading divine

692
00:34:51,900 --> 00:34:54,360
 into this uncharted area?

693
00:34:54,360 --> 00:34:56,400
 As part of the kingdom's advisement

694
00:34:56,400 --> 00:34:58,640
 in His grand plan for Hong Kong,

695
00:34:58,640 --> 00:35:02,660
 we felt led by the spirit to narrow our focus

696
00:35:02,660 --> 00:35:04,700
 to reaching out to local Cantonese speakers

697
00:35:04,700 --> 00:35:07,240
 as well as Mandarin speakers who have settled

698
00:35:07,240 --> 00:35:10,400
 or are settling to integrate with the broader community

699
00:35:10,400 --> 00:35:12,080
 here in Hong Kong.

700
00:35:12,080 --> 00:35:15,120
 We want to be part of the new and developing community

701
00:35:15,120 --> 00:35:18,320
 that will grow and mature in years to come.

702
00:35:18,320 --> 00:35:21,620
 Still, we want to start now,

703
00:35:21,620 --> 00:35:25,180
 operating from possibly Shaanxi as a base

704
00:35:25,180 --> 00:35:28,260
 for outreach efforts, discipleship,

705
00:35:28,260 --> 00:35:30,160
 and small group developments.

706
00:35:30,160 --> 00:35:33,240
 In fact, while the real estate sentiment

707
00:35:33,240 --> 00:35:36,060
 was really at rock bottom last year,

708
00:35:36,060 --> 00:35:40,160
 our family made a small, bold move

709
00:35:40,160 --> 00:35:43,440
 to move from the island side to the new territories.

710
00:35:43,440 --> 00:35:49,180
 I used to walk, no, I used to take three minutes lift,

711
00:35:49,180 --> 00:35:53,940
 okay, from the hospital quarters to the hospital,

712
00:35:53,940 --> 00:35:57,440
 which is right opposite, to attend to my patients.

713
00:35:57,440 --> 00:36:02,200
 These days, I drove 50 to 60 minutes to commute to work.

714
00:36:02,200 --> 00:36:05,680
 But now we have the benefit of reaching North Metropolis

715
00:36:05,680 --> 00:36:08,840
 in 20 minutes and the border in 25 minutes.

716
00:36:08,840 --> 00:36:13,160
 While we are convinced that God will honor our commitments

717
00:36:13,160 --> 00:36:17,480
 to avail ourselves, we want to develop small groups

718
00:36:17,480 --> 00:36:22,000
 as the basis for many interlinking building blocks

719
00:36:22,000 --> 00:36:24,460
 for fellow believers who may be dispersed

720
00:36:24,460 --> 00:36:29,020
 over a wide stretch of land throughout North Metropolis.

721
00:36:29,020 --> 00:36:33,340
 And yet, we decide to be united with the vine

722
00:36:33,340 --> 00:36:36,540
 as we share the pulpit messages from the vine

723
00:36:36,540 --> 00:36:40,040
 as anchors for our Sunday gatherings.

724
00:36:40,040 --> 00:36:43,400
 We may be starting small, but we plant the seeds,

725
00:36:43,400 --> 00:36:49,140
 we water the plants, and may God grow and transform lives.

726
00:36:50,440 --> 00:36:53,920
 We pray that we'll continue to see lives being renewed

727
00:36:53,920 --> 00:36:56,780
 and transformed through this church plant.

728
00:36:56,780 --> 00:37:00,680
 >> Earlier, I shared my faith journey began

729
00:37:00,680 --> 00:37:03,460
 in an English-speaking community.

730
00:37:03,460 --> 00:37:07,740
 My theological training was entirely English-based.

731
00:37:07,740 --> 00:37:11,560
 I had no connections with the local churches in Hong Kong

732
00:37:11,560 --> 00:37:14,940
 and little understanding of the religious sentiments

733
00:37:14,940 --> 00:37:15,820
 in China.

734
00:37:17,280 --> 00:37:20,840
 I didn't even have the Christian vocabulary

735
00:37:20,840 --> 00:37:24,560
 or prayer language in Cantonese and Mandarin.

736
00:37:24,560 --> 00:37:28,840
 So, when God gave me that vision more than 10 years ago

737
00:37:28,840 --> 00:37:32,080
 to reach out to the local Chinese community,

738
00:37:32,080 --> 00:37:34,740
 I felt completely unqualified.

739
00:37:34,740 --> 00:37:40,360
 I felt like Jeremiah in chapter one saying,

740
00:37:40,360 --> 00:37:43,200
 "I do not know how to speak.

741
00:37:43,200 --> 00:37:47,920
 "How possibly could I serve the Chinese?"

742
00:37:47,920 --> 00:37:54,140
 I saw all my inadequacies, my lack of fluency,

743
00:37:54,140 --> 00:37:59,280
 my unfamiliarity of the local Christian culture,

744
00:37:59,280 --> 00:38:02,660
 my limited experience, the list goes on.

745
00:38:02,660 --> 00:38:06,980
 My heart was overwhelmed.

746
00:38:06,980 --> 00:38:11,980
 But looking back now, I realize those places of weakness

747
00:38:12,480 --> 00:38:17,080
 were where God was inviting me to surrender,

748
00:38:17,080 --> 00:38:18,900
 to surrender, to surrender.

749
00:38:18,900 --> 00:38:24,760
 What I saw as a limitation, God embraced as an invitation.

750
00:38:24,760 --> 00:38:30,280
 An invitation for His presence to reach us and to lead,

751
00:38:30,280 --> 00:38:34,520
 His strength to see us through

752
00:38:34,520 --> 00:38:39,060
 and to make known His love for the Chinese.

753
00:38:39,060 --> 00:38:43,640
 Not by my ability, but by His calling and grace.

754
00:38:43,640 --> 00:38:47,600
 And now, as we step into this next uncharted season

755
00:38:47,600 --> 00:38:51,440
 as a church, we feel that same call again

756
00:38:51,440 --> 00:38:56,120
 to enter a new frontier with boldness, courage,

757
00:38:56,120 --> 00:38:59,320
 and humility to reach out to the Chinese

758
00:38:59,320 --> 00:39:01,700
 in a new context, in a new era.

759
00:39:01,700 --> 00:39:04,800
 Not from a place of confidence,

760
00:39:04,800 --> 00:39:09,800
 but from vulnerability, authenticity, and love.

761
00:39:09,800 --> 00:39:12,160
 Do we have all the answers?

762
00:39:12,160 --> 00:39:13,000
 No.

763
00:39:13,000 --> 00:39:18,000
 But we are going, not because the path is clear,

764
00:39:18,000 --> 00:39:20,760
 but because the Spirit is leading.

765
00:39:20,760 --> 00:39:25,760
 >> We dare to believe when we do God's work

766
00:39:25,760 --> 00:39:28,340
 in God's way and in God's timing,

767
00:39:28,340 --> 00:39:30,520
 we always see God's fruits.

768
00:39:30,520 --> 00:39:34,160
 So how should this congregation respond?

769
00:39:34,160 --> 00:39:38,600
 Number one, well, don't belittle yourself

770
00:39:38,600 --> 00:39:40,240
 as an English speaker.

771
00:39:40,240 --> 00:39:44,520
 Prayerfully discern that God could be igniting

772
00:39:44,520 --> 00:39:46,920
 a passion for you to reach out

773
00:39:46,920 --> 00:39:49,100
 to the Chinese speakers in the land.

774
00:39:49,100 --> 00:39:53,080
 And then you think of your time, your talents,

775
00:39:53,080 --> 00:39:56,080
 and your treasures that God has entrusted to you,

776
00:39:56,080 --> 00:40:00,560
 which you may contribute to this vision.

777
00:40:00,560 --> 00:40:03,120
 The operating model of this New River Initiative

778
00:40:03,120 --> 00:40:06,040
 is that lots of the ministry will be led

779
00:40:06,040 --> 00:40:08,800
 by volunteers and lay leaders.

780
00:40:08,800 --> 00:40:12,720
 And I'm privileged to be one of these paid,

781
00:40:12,720 --> 00:40:15,240
 no, not paid, lay leaders.

782
00:40:15,240 --> 00:40:17,100
 [laughing]

783
00:40:17,100 --> 00:40:19,720
 Well, we want to take the time to grow the community

784
00:40:19,720 --> 00:40:21,880
 in relationship to in discipleship

785
00:40:21,880 --> 00:40:24,360
 and in readiness to reach out.

786
00:40:24,360 --> 00:40:28,040
 While we discern and identify the appropriate venue

787
00:40:28,040 --> 00:40:32,840
 for gathering, both in the interim as well as the midterm,

788
00:40:32,840 --> 00:40:36,120
 when more of Northern Metropolis facilities

789
00:40:36,120 --> 00:40:39,400
 and venues may become available.

